# Google Gemini API Configuration
# ================================
# 
# Get your API key from: https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
# 
# For Local Development:
# 1. Copy this file: cp .env.example .env.local
# 2. Add your actual Gemini API key to .env.local
# 3. The .env.local file is in .gitignore and won't be committed
# 
# For Vercel Deployment:
# 1. Go to your Vercel project dashboard
# 2. Navigate to Settings → Environment Variables
# 3. Add the variable name: GEMINI_API_KEY
# 4. Paste your actual Gemini API key as the value
# 5. Select "Production", "Preview", and "Development" environments
# 6. Click "Save" and redeploy your project
# 
# Security Notes:
# - NEVER commit .env.local to version control
# - NEVER expose API keys in frontend/client-side code
# - ONLY use API keys in backend API routes (/app/api/*)
# - API keys are automatically redacted from Vercel logs
# - For debugging, see logs at: vercel.com/dashboard → your-project → deployments

GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here
